-- slice 6 / EMITTER-GAPS #18 E23 (value facet): pass a `=>`-CONSTRAINED named
-- function as a FIRST-CLASS VALUE to a higher-order function.  `isEv : Integral a
-- => a -> Bool` (via `%` and `==`) is dict-passed by elaboration, so a bare
-- occurrence lowers to a `CDict "isEv" routes` node — NOT a plain `CVar`/eta
-- closure.  Used as a value (the `f` arg of `pick`, not the head of a saturated
-- call), it must become a closure that captures its constraint dict route(s) and
-- forwards them ahead of the value args to @mdk_isEv when `pick` invokes it
-- indirectly.  Before the fix the emitter hit its emitExpr catch-all →
-- "unsupported Core IR node CDict"; the interpreter was always correct, so a green
-- build here proves run==build for a constrained-fn HOF argument.  `isEv 4` is True
-- ⇒ 100 (an Int result keeps the golden render unambiguous).
isEv x = x % 2 == 0
pick f y = if f y then 100 else 200
main = pick isEv 4
